It was moving toward the west at nearly 20 mph.
A tropical storm warning was posted for the southeastern Bahamas and the nearby British Turks and Caicos islands.
It was too early to tell if the storm would threaten the Bahamas, which lie far north of other Caribbean islands.
Boca Raton's residents may be less concerned.
``It's capable of almost catastrophic destruction,'' said Todd Kimberlain, a forecaster at the hurricane center.
A hurricane watch on the mainland was extended from the Miami area northward all the way to near Brunswick, Ga.